<subSubSection id="C368C7A86F54FFB90BFCFECBFEB9FC81" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BCD94236F54FFB90BFCFECBFE9FFED9" blockId="42.[189,303,267,293]" box="[189,303,267,293]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<heading id="D085234F6F54FFB90BFCFECBFE9FFED9" bold="true" box="[189,303,267,293]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B90648316F54FFB90BFCFECBFE9FFED9" bold="true" box="[189,303,267,293]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD94236F54FFB90BFCFEF9FDC8FDB6" blockId="42.[189,1399,313,586]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
The 
<typeStatus id="54C92A816F54FFB90BB4FEF9FEECFEAF" box="[245,348,313,339]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F54FFB90AC9FEFAFD8EFEAF" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[392,574,313,339]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obtusiconus">
<emphasis id="B90648316F54FFB90AC9FEFAFD8EFEAF" box="[392,574,313,339]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">M. obtusiconus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry id="F365D4B36F54FFB909D2FEFAFD7CFEA8" box="[659,716,314,340]" name="Peru" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Peru</collectingCountry>
, and the specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="F365D4B36F54FFB908B8FEF9FBDDFEAF" box="[1017,1133,313,339]" name="Colombia" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Colombia</collectingCountry>
differ in a number of details, including the distal fore tarsomeres (white in the Colombian specimen, dark in the type) and the colour of the metapleuron and hind coxa (red in the Colombian specimen, black in the type). Both specimens, however, share several distinctive characters, such as the colour of the mid and hind femora, the broad postocellar part of the frontal vitta, a similar pattern of silvery pruinosity on the scutum and a similarly reddish abdominal base. Furthermore, they easily key out together because of the distinctive femoral colour. More specimens of this species (or species group) are needed to clarify what variation is intraspecific and what is interspecific.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD94236F54FFB90BFCFDB1FB35FD09" blockId="42.[189,1399,625,757]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
This is one of the five species originally described in 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F54FFB9086DFDB2FC08FD77" box="[812,952,626,651]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90648316F54FFB9086DFDB2FC08FD77" box="[812,952,626,651]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Mesoconius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
solely on the basis of specimens from Callanga, 
<collectingCountry id="F365D4B36F54FFB90A75FD55FEDEFD53" box="[308,366,661,687]" name="Peru" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Peru</collectingCountry>
. Two remain known only from the 
<typeStatus id="54C92A816F54FFB90846FD55FCF9FD53" box="[775,841,661,687]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">types</typeStatus>
. The other three, 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F54FFB90F55FD55FB77FD52" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[1044,1223,660,686]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obtusiconus">
<emphasis id="B90648316F54FFB90F55FD55FB77FD52" box="[1044,1223,660,686]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">M. obtusiconus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<treatmentCitation id="0AD3B2326F54FFB90F94FD55FECFFD2E" accessDate="2019-07-23" author="Enderlein" authority="Enderlein, 1922" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" firstAuthor="Enderlein" genus="Mesoconius" journalOrPublisher="Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="140 - 229" part="88" phylum="Arthropoda" publicationUrl="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/45506103" rank="species" refId="ref59018" refString="Enderlein G. 1922. Klassifikation der Micropeziden. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A 88 (5): 140 - 229. Available from https: // biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 45506103 [accessed 23 Jul. 2019]." species="albimanus" title="Klassifikation der Micropeziden" treatmentTaxon="M. albimanus" type="journal article" year="1922">
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F54FFB90F94FD55FECFFD2E" authority="Enderlein, 1922" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albimanus">
<emphasis id="B90648316F54FFB90F94FD55FAC6FD52" box="[1237,1398,660,686]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">M. albimanus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE3E9D26F54FFB90BFCFD78FECFFD2E" accessDate="2019-07-23" author="Enderlein" box="[189,383,696,722]" firstAuthor="Enderlein" journalOrPublisher="Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="140 - 229" part="88" publicationUrl="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/45506103" refId="ref59018" refString="Enderlein G. 1922. Klassifikation der Micropeziden. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A 88 (5): 140 - 229. Available from https: // biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 45506103 [accessed 23 Jul. 2019]." title="Klassifikation der Micropeziden" type="journal article" year="1922">Enderlein, 1922</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
and 
<treatmentCitation id="0AD3B2326F54FFB90A85FD78FCABFD2E" accessDate="2019-07-23" author="Enderlein" authority="Enderlein, 1922" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[452,795,696,722]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" firstAuthor="Enderlein" genus="Mesoconius" journalOrPublisher="Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="140 - 229" part="88" phylum="Arthropoda" publicationUrl="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/45506103" rank="species" refId="ref59018" refString="Enderlein G. 1922. Klassifikation der Micropeziden. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A 88 (5): 140 - 229. Available from https: // biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 45506103 [accessed 23 Jul. 2019]." species="infestus" title="Klassifikation der Micropeziden" treatmentTaxon="M. infestus" type="journal article" year="1922">
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F54FFB90A85FD78FCABFD2E" authority="Enderlein, 1922" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[452,795,696,722]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infestus">
<emphasis id="B90648316F54FFB90A85FD78FDFCFD2E" box="[452,588,696,722]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">M. infestus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE3E9D26F54FFB90918FD78FCABFD2E" accessDate="2019-07-23" author="Enderlein" box="[601,795,696,722]" firstAuthor="Enderlein" journalOrPublisher="Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="140 - 229" part="88" publicationUrl="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/45506103" refId="ref59018" refString="Enderlein G. 1922. Klassifikation der Micropeziden. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte A 88 (5): 140 - 229. Available from https: // biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 45506103 [accessed 23 Jul. 2019]." title="Klassifikation der Micropeziden" type="journal article" year="1922">Enderlein, 1922</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
present similar problems because of differences between the Callanga material and putatively conspecific material from 
<collectingCountry id="F365D4B36F54FFB90F4BFD1BFB32FD09" box="[1034,1154,731,757]" name="Colombia" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Colombia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD94236F54FFB90BFCFCDDFEB9FC81" blockId="42.[189,1399,796,893]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F54FFB90BFCFCDDFE6CFCCA" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1922" box="[189,476,796,822]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obtusiconus">
<emphasis id="B90648316F54FFB90BFCFCDDFE6CFCCA" box="[189,476,796,822]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Mesoconius obtusiconus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unusual because the absence of a postocellar bristle places it in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F54FFB90E4CFCDDFAC7FCCA" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Schiner" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[1293,1399,797,822]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eques">
<emphasis id="B90648316F54FFB90E4CFCDDFAC7FCCA" box="[1293,1399,797,822]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">M. eques</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, but the relatively flat katatergite and the spermathecal complex resemble those of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F54FFB90FBEFC80FAC7FCA5" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Hennig" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[1279,1399,831,857]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oblitus">
<emphasis id="B90648316F54FFB90FBEFC80FAC7FCA5" box="[1279,1399,831,857]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">M. oblitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group.
</paragraph>
